    "body": "## Description\r\nCloses https://github.com/NVIDIA/cccl/issues/5675 \r\n@elstehle and I are working on adding a device-level top-K algorithm into CUB. \r\n\r\n## Notes to reviewers\r\n\r\nThis initial implementation is limited in scope to return the results unsorted and, in the presence of tied keys across the k-th position, return non-deterministic results (i.e., when there are the same keys across the k-th output position, which of these items make it into the top-k result are chosen randomly).\r\n\r\n#### Ready for review:\r\n\r\n- **Tests:**\r\n  - cub/test/catch2_test_device_topk_api.cu\r\n  - cub/test/catch2_test_device_topk_common.cuh\r\n  - cub/test/catch2_test_device_topk_keys.cu\r\n  - cub/test/catch2_test_device_topk_pairs.cu\r\n\r\n- **Interface:**\r\n  - cub/cub/device/device_topk.cuh\r\n  - cub/cub/cub.cuh\r\n  - cub/examples/device/example_device_topk_keys.cu\r\n  - cub/examples/device/example_device_topk_pairs.cu\r\n\r\n- **Benchmarks:**\r\n  - cub/benchmarks/bench/topk/keys.cu\r\n  - cub/benchmarks/bench/topk/pairs.cu\r\n\r\n- **Implementation:**\r\n  - cub/cub/device/dispatch/dispatch_topk.cuh\r\n  - cub/cub/device/agent/agent_topk.cuh\r\n\r\n### About this topK parallel algorithm\r\nThe top-K problem requires selecting the K largest or smallest elements from an unsorted list.   \r\n\r\nAs a fundamental challenge in computer science, the top-K algorithm plays a crucial role in many applications, such as Approximate Nearest Neighbor (ANN) algorithms in vector databases, sampling in Stable Diffusion, Mixture of Experts (MoE), speculative sampling, top-K sampling in large language models, and high-throughput virtual screening.\r\n\r\nWe propose a parallel top-K algorithm called AIR Top-K (Adaptive and Iteration-fused Radix Top-K). As a multi-pass algorithm that iterates over the elements’ radix digits, processing one digit per pass. Each pass comprises three major steps: compute the histogram over the current digit values, find the target digit with the kth element, and filter candidates by target digit. 1) We propose to fuse filtering for the current pass and histogram computation for the next pass in a single kernel, which considerably reduces the amount of memory transfers. 2) We design an adaptive strategy that automatically alters buffering behavior based on data distribution to avoid superfluous memory traffic.\r\n\r\nThis work was published in the SC conference [Parallel Top-K Algorithms on GPU: A Comprehensive Study and New Methods](https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3581784.3607062). \r\n\r\n## Unit tests and examples\r\n### Unit tests:\r\n```\r\ncub/test/catch2_test_device_topk_keys.cu\r\ncub/test/catch2_test_device_topk_pairs.cu\r\n```\r\n### Example:\r\n```\r\ncub/examples/device/example_device_topk_keys.cu\r\ncub/examples/device/example_device_topk_pairs.cu\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Completed\r\n\r\n- [x] Support arbitrary `k` values instead of failing at runtime\r\n- [x] Test more corner cases with regards to `k` and `num_items`\r\n- [x] Investigate and fix for `k==num_items`\r\n- [x]  Investigate and fix for `k==1`\r\n- [x] Move shared memory histogram to `temporary_storage`\r\n- [x] Use an `enum class` instead of `bool` to specify whether to select `min` or `max`\r\n- [x] Take stream via `environment` \r\n- [x] Clean up tests for top-k keys\r\n- [x] Clean up tests for top-k pairs\r\n- [x] Move examples to catch2 api tests\r\n- [x] Update examples to pass the right environment parameters\r\n- [x] Update benchmarks to pass the right environment parameters\r\n- [x] Add `output_ordering` to the requirements API\r\n- [x] Fail for configurations that are not supported by initial implementation (i.e., require to have `determinism` to be `not_guaranteed` and `output_order` to be `unsorted`)\r\n- [x] In our tests, make `min`/`max` selection a compile-time option via `type_list` instead of a runtime option\r\n\r\n## Scoped for follow-up work/PR\r\n- [ ] Extract first histogram-only pass into own kernel\r\n- [ ] Add [work stealing](https://nvidia.github.io/cccl/libcudacxx/extended_api/work_stealing.html) to `process_range`",
